HEADWORD: Forlay
<hw>For*lay"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>for-</ets> + <ets>lay</ets>.]</ety> <def>To lie in wait for; to
ambush.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An ambushed thief <qex>forlays</qex> a traveler.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forleave</ent>⟦br⟧
